{{see|triangulum}}

==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[triangulum]]'', a "[[triangle]]"
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Triangulum'''

#{{constellation}}: An [[autumn]] [[constellation]] of the [[northern]] sky whose brightest three [[star]]s form a small [[triangle]]. The constellation lies near [[Perseus]], between [[Aries]] and [[Andromeda]].
#{{astronomy}}: The [[Triangulum Galaxy]], a relatively nearby [[spiral]] [[galaxy]] to the [[Milky Way]]; [[M33]].

